<catsoop-section>Instructions</catsoop-section>

**Assembly:**

Take out all the pieces from the MDF sheet. Join 6 faces to form a cube, then repeat with all 48 small square pieces to create 8 small cubes, ensuring the **IITGN logo** and **CCL logo** are on opposite sides of each cube. Connect 2 square pieces and 8 rectangular pieces to construct a box large enough to contain all the cubes.

**How to Play:**

The puzzle begins with 8 cubes inside the box, leaving one central space empty. Movement initiates with the middle cubes of each side, unlocking adjacent positions with each move.

The aim is to rearrange the cubes until each side displays the CCL logo, replacing the IIT Gandhinagar logo if it was previously on top, or vice versa. The middle space should remain empty.

